column1: Owners are required to clean up and dispose of your dog's droppings in all public areas. Poo bags and bins are installed in some parks and gardens in both on-leash and off-leash areas.Dogs must be kept under control by means of a chain, cord or leash, which is no more than three metres in length.Dogs must be on a leash if they are within 20 metres of a children's playground.Dogs must remain on the leash near fountains, ponds and lakes and not enter any body of water. They are prohibited from the entire precinct of Trin Warren Tam-boore, the recycling wetland in Royal Park.
column8: Childers Street, Kensington, City of Melbourne, Victoria, 3031, Australia
